review_blob: Great dark pour with thick, light brown head. slight caramel aroma. great creamy feel. good rich malt taste with hints of fruit and coffee. i would recommend this beer to anyone.
nice roasted malt flavor with hints of coffee. thick, dark pour with nice off-white head. strong and delicious.
Strong coffee flavor. good dark pour with nice chocolate/coffee scent. heavy and delicious.
From bottle. Pours translucent light gold with small head. aroma is a little flowery. tastes clean and crisp with a sweet perfume/flower taste to it.. finishes clean.
pours a hazy gold with small head. nice citrus smell and taste with an interesting spice to the end of it. best wheat sam adams makes.
Nice puffy white head with slight citrus aroma. tastes slightly citrus. overall slightly above average
standard Mexican beer. goes good with lime. recommend drinking after downing some margaritas so you dont taste it.
Pours a hazy gold with small white head. Rich aroma where you can smell the citrus and spices. Tastes stong of yeast with hint of fruit. Clean mouth feel. Leaves light lace on glass.
Decently smooth lager. Nothing exceptional about it. Very thick, white head adds to appearance. Clear golden color, with a smooth finish

this lager has a slightly fruity taste you cant quite define. it has a nice golden color and crisp, fruity scent that makes this beer perfect for hanging out outside in the sun. a very light beer that i could drink all day long.
Strong rye scent with nice hoppiness to compliment. slight orange/citrus scent that adds to an enjoyable overall beer.
nice golden color with strong fruity aroma. alcohol is noticeable. overall fruity taste with nice balance of hops and maltiness. good beer overall. worth trying.
very strong on flavor. hazy golden color with strong, tantalizing aroma. mild webbing left of glass. rich hops, mixed with a citrus aftertaste. clean finish.
beer_name: Boulder Beer Hazed Hoppy Session Ale

review_blob: the best beer served at the cafe. decent red color with a rich aroma. the small head did not last more than a minute. nothing extraordinary in the taste but nothing wrong with it either. worth trying but nothing to get excited over.
smelled better than it tasted. not terrible but i was unimpressed. coffee flavors mingle with the hops, but leave you wishing the coffee taste would just go away.
beer_name: Karibrew Down Town Nut Brown Ale

review_blob: highly mediocre. has a soapy, sweet smell, with an unimpressive head. Better that most mass produced beer, but i was left wanting something more.

delicious full bodied beer. deep dark color, with a nice thick head that does not go away. leaves solid rings/lacing on the glass while drinking it. nice rich flavor with hints of coffee and chocolate. and over all rich and fulfilling beer.

good beer but i was expecting more. it has a nice dark red-brown appearance and by the time i received my beer, the head was nonexistent. other that that, it had a good balance of malt and hops with a clean finish.
tastes bad. smells bad. if you drink a lot of it you will feel very bad in the morning. very watery and light with a taste that leaves you desiring a lot. not worth drinking.

slightly more hops than expected for a red, but it works well. nice piney aroma, and pours a rich red-brown color. nice balance between the malt and the hops with a slightly earthy taste. leaves you feeling refreshed and wanting more.
good unfiltered wheat. nice hazy golden color with an off white head. you can taste a hint of citrus in the beer but it is not overpowering.
nice fruity flavor but was too carbonated for me. i could not even taste the hops. had a decent crisp finish.
might as well drink water. dont waste your time even trying this one. it is a waste of space in the fridge and in your stomach
a nice aroma comes from this hazy-golden colored brew. decent hops in the flavor but not overpowering. overall, it is nothing spectacular but nice to see something different from shock top.

not much better that the light version, which is hardly worth drinking. only drink if no other beer is available. the one thing it has going for it is it is slightly better that water, but not by much

pours very pale. lacking taste and aroma. a very watery beer. leaves you wanting. only good if you are trying to drink a lot of beer in a very short period of time, or if you find yourself wandering the streets of mexico with no idea how you got there or where you are going.
Pours a dark brown. a nice mix of maltiness and bitterness, with a nice clean finish. this is a beer you can drink all night and never feel like you need more.
Good dark ale. great flavor with a good thick head. nothing extraordinary but still worth having.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: a light gold color in glass. decent head that lingers. decently strong hops but not overpowering. has a slight breadiness and a crisp, clean finish.

perfect combination of blueberry taste with nice, rich blueberry/hoppy aroma. not too sweet, can clearly taste the blueberry but it is not over powering. perfect beer to drink while enjoying a nice summer evening outdoors

If you are looking for something very fruity, this will do it. it was too sweet for my taste and way too much carbonation. the aroma is rich and fruity, but i would recomend sweetwater blue over this if you are looking for blueberry beer.
Great full head, nice aroma, and good appearance. very dark and you can taste the chocolate. delicious beer, very filling, and an overall above average stout
not much to say. if you have ever had one, you already know... good if you are in college celebrating a win, or drinking away your sorrows. serves no other purpose.
Standard Pale Ale. good color, light, and refreshing. not very much taste. in every way an average Pale Ale
Not bad, but nothing special. crisp taste with maybe too much carbonation. decent aroma but nothing to get excited over.
